We are currently looking for a Data Engineer for our business intelligence project in healthcare domain.

Does this relate to you?
• 3+ years experience in creating custom reports that pull from various data sources, including Google Sheets, Excel, SQL databases, and platform APIs;
• At least 3+ years of experience using Python;
• Strong knowledge in writing queries in MySQL;
• Excellent Google Sheets/Excel skills;
• 5+ years experience in ETL processes and techniques;
• 5+ years of data hygiene experience;
• Strong conceptual, communication, and technical skills.
• Analytical thinking, solution-oriented, ability to demonstrate a passion for data and data analysis;
• Upper-Intermediate level of English.

Nice to have:
• Experience using Looker, Knowi and BigQuery;
• Experience with migration of user base between platforms;
• Ability to work 8 AM to 12 PM MST, and attend relevant meetings during that time;
• Ability... to autonomously work to remove blockers as they arise - initiating and following through on lines of communication with project managers and other stakeholders throughout the org.

About the project:
This is a trans healthcare project for trans women and trans men. It offers gender-affirming healthcare services in 37 states to anybody between the ages of 18 and 65.

A new team member will be in charge of:
• Evaluate customer analytics needs and offer possible solutions in the Healthcare field;
• Understand the required input data for analysis and create a conceptual model of a Business Intelligence solution;
• Create client-driven dashboards and reports for decision-making and performance monitoring using Business Intelligence tools;
• Interview end users to determine requirements for data, reports, analyses, training, data quality and performance;
• Work with data warehouse architects to translate requirements into technical specifications;
• Offer your vision on how to improve and make data analysis more convenient in the future;
• Ensuring ongoing data hygiene.

What we offer:
• Fully paid English classes with an in-house English teacher
• 20 paid days off per year in total
• Flexible schedule
• Regular performance reviews
• Training and IT certification
• Special occasion bonuses (birthday, marriage, childbirth)

Ready to try your hand? Send your CV without a doubt
